= doc_title(title: "Links", comp: @comp) do |title|
  %p
    Tailwind removes the styling on standard links so we provide an easy way to
    re-add them. This works very similarly to the
    = link_to "link_to", "https://api.rubyonrails.org/classes/ActionView/Helpers/UrlHelper.html#method-i-link_to", class: "font-mono"
    helper in Rails.


= doc_example(title: "Basic Links") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      Basic links are styled with the `.link` class. The `title` and `href`
      options can be passed as keyword arguments, or as the first two positional
      arguments.

      The `title` can also be passed as a block.

  .flex.items-end.space-x-4
    = daisy_link title: "Home", href: "#"
    = daisy_link "Docs", "#", css: "link-primary text-xl"
    = daisy_link "Components", "#", css: "link-secondary text-2xl"
    = daisy_link "#", css: "link-success link-hover text-3xl" do
      Big Hover Link

= doc_example(title: "Links with Icons") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      Links support the same `icon`, `left_icon`, and `right_icon` options as
      buttons. Icons are rendered using Hero Icons and are automatically sized
      and aligned with the link text.

  .flex.items-end.space-x-4
    = daisy_link(title: "Home", href: "#", icon: "home")
    = daisy_link(title: "Download", href: "#", css: "link-primary", left_icon: "arrow-down-tray")
    = daisy_link(title: "Next", href: "#", css: "link-secondary", right_icon: "arrow-right")
    = daisy_link(title: "Transfer", href: "#", css: "link-accent", left_icon: "arrow-left", right_icon: "arrow-right")
